casebody.data:
Thursday, January 3, 2002

MISCELLANEOUS DISMISSALS

01-2141. Cross v. Krishnan.

Montgomery App. No. 18772. This cause is pending before the court as a discretionary appeal. Upon consideration of appellants’ application for dismissal,

IT IS ORDERED by the court that the application for dismissal be, and hereby is, granted.

ACCORDINGLY, IT IS FURTHER ORDERED by the court that this cause be, and hereby is, dismissed.
